Simple HTML Calculator Story Point 94.5

You are going to create a simple calculator that can Add, Subtract, and Multiply.

**Requirements:**

01. - You will have one section (`<div>`) for each math operation (so 3 sections) total

02. - Each section has two inputs to take the first and second numbers

03. - Each section will have a button to perform the operation

04. - You will inject the result into the HTML (not an alert)

05. - Your website will have 3 colors

06. - Your website will have proper padding/spacing to lay things out nicely

